The paper discusses a novel I/O cache load balancing scheme for high-performance servers, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The proposed scheme involves managing the write policy of the cache, which is related to Operating Systems (cs.OS) and Architecture (cs.AR). The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed scheme using a physical system, which is related to Databases (cs.DB) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
